<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1579,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1579,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Irregularly massive sponges, typically cream, grey, black, or yellow in colour. Microspined microxeas and/or microrhabds are arranged more-or-less tangentially at the surface of the sponge, forming a crust. Megascleres are oxeas and short- to medium-shafted dicho-, ortho- or plagiotriaenes that form a layer under or above the cortex, cladomes uppermost. Oxeas are arranged more-or-less radially in the upper choanosome but are usually disorganised below the subectosome. Microscleres are smooth microxeas and/or blunt-ended microrhabds that may or may not be centrotylote; microspined or smooth euasters (oxyasters, tylasters), spherules and spherasters are sometimes present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1579,2039]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,152,647]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1832,1858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
In his original concept of the geodiid subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority=", Sollas" authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[890,1070,1832,1858]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae, Sollas</taxonomicName>
included only 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1247,1386,1832,1858]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1320,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Erylus</emphasis>
Gray
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,354,1868,1895]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Caminus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,251,1869,1895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Caminus</emphasis>
Schmidt
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[408,657,1868,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[519,568,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
found strong molecular support for inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bowerbank in Johnson" authorityName="Bowerbank in Johnston" authorityYear="1842" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Pachymatisma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1367,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachymatisma</emphasis>
Bowerbank in Johnson
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[405,496,1905,1930]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,496,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[529,628,1904,1930]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[637,882,1904,1931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[747,795,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the main skeletal characters that define 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[151,246,1940,1966]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[262,503,1940,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[377,435,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[516,585,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,946,971]" captionTargetBox="[477,1112,179,926]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[470,1116,174,934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distribution of P. schulzei (Dendy 1905), around New Zealand. The white outline shows New Zealand’s Exclusive Economic Zone." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335266/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), which amounted to a series of ‘losses,’ including the lack of anatriaenes, protriaenes and cortical oxeas (of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[525,642,1976,2003]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geodiinae">Geodiinae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[683,756,1976,2002]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[683,756,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[768,868,1977,2003]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Caminus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[768,868,1977,2003]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Caminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank in Johnston" authorityYear="1842" box="[920,1085,1976,2002]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Pachymatisma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[920,1085,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachymatisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[1141,1425,1975,2002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[151,246,2012,2038]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
are now defined as having short-shafted triaenes (although this is not strictly true with the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly, 2015" authorityName="Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,708,152,179]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Pachymatisma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis box="[151,405,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pachymatisma nodosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[413,708,152,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), microrhabds in the ectocortex (outer cortex), with spherules in the ectocortex being specific to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[508,608,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Caminus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[508,608,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Caminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and aspidasters to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cardenas et al. 2010)" authorityName="Cardenas" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Cardenas" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[821,1153,189,215]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,894,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Erylus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[908,1145,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[1021,1078,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Although supported by molecular studies, the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[861,952,226,251]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,952,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Sollas" authorityYear="1888" box="[989,1087,225,251]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erylinae">Erylinae</taxonomicName>
, implies the major synapomorphies, i.e., the loss of protriaenes and anatriaenes, and the loss of sterrasters/aspidasters in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1190,1308,261,287]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Geodiidae</taxonomicName>
, have been secondarily lost in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[368,459,298,323]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,459,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[520,776,297,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[633,690,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. Similarly, inclusion of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1049,1185,298,323]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis box="[1049,1185,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. euastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which contains aspidasters) within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[321,412,334,359]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,412,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S." box="[469,697,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="89 - 106" refId="ref26383" refString="Cardenas, P., Rapp, H. T., Schander, C. &amp; Tendal, O. S. (2010) Molecular taxonomy and phylogeny of Geodiidae (Porifera, Demospongiae, Astrophorida) - combining phylogenetic and Linnaean classification. Zoologica Scripta, 39, 89 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2009.00402. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis box="[579,634,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
) means that there is no morphological character that can be used to definitively separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[384,475,370,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[384,475,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[540,613,369,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[540,613,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in a practical sense (
<bibRefCitation author="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M." box="[848,1134,368,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref28068" refString="Sim-Smith, C. &amp; Kelly, M. (2015) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Sponges in the Family Geodiidae (Demospongiae: Astrophorina). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir 128. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research Ltd, Wellington, 102 pp." type="book" year="2015">Sim-Smith &amp; Kelly 2015</bibRefCitation>
). We question the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[181,316,406,431]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis box="[181,316,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E. euastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[401,492,406,431]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,492,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for practical purposes, while keeping the two genera separate, and believe the more molecular evidence is needed to support these decisions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
In the meantime, we will continue to use the traditional, positive concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1070,1161,478,503]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1070,1161,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., 
<bibRefCitation author="Uriz, M. J." box="[1228,1358,477,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="134 - 140" refId="ref28586" refString="Uriz, M. J. (2002 b) Family Geodiidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Soest, R. W. M. van (Eds.), Systema Porifera: A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 134 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 14" type="book chapter" year="2002">Uriz 2002b</bibRefCitation>
) to assign new species, i.e., that these are sponges with a thin crust-forming cortex composed of smooth microrhabds that may or may not be centrotylote. In addition, the species possess short- to long-shafted dichotriaenes, orthotriaenes or plagiotriaenes and oxeas as megascleres, and the microsclere complement of microxeas and microrhabds may include euasters.
</paragraph>
